articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Igor Girkin, a prominent ultranationalist in custody in Russia awaiting trial on charges of inciting extremism, nominated himself to run for president in 2024 in an announcement read on his behalf on Saturday, the online SOTA news channel said.
articles.title: Jailed Russian nationalist nominates himself for president

articles.author: Raul Cadenas  Susana Vera
articles.description: About 170,000 people marched through Madrid on Saturday in the largest protest yet against an amnesty law which Spain's Socialists agreed over Catalonia's 2017 separatist bid in order to form a government.
articles.title: Biggest protest in Spain against Catalan amnesty law draws 170,000

articles.author: Brendan O'Boyle
articles.description: International rebuke swelled on Saturday over what observers say are efforts to use a politicized justice system to keep Guatemalan President-elect Bernardo Arevalo out of office.
articles.title: International backlash grows after move to strip Guatemalan president-elect's immunity

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: A young Brazilian fan of U.S. singer Taylor Swift died in Rio de Janeiro on Friday night after falling ill inside the sweltering stadium where the superstar's concert was held, amid a record-breaking heat-wave across large swathes of Brazil.
articles.title: Fan dies at Taylor Swift show in sweltering Rio de Janeiro

articles.author: Anne Kauranen
articles.description: Dozens of migrants stood behind barriers at two crossings on Finland's border with Russia on Saturday, the Finnish Border Guard said, after Helsinki erected barricades to halt a flow of asylum seekers it says was instigated by Moscow.
articles.title: Dozens of migrants wait at Finland-Russia border after Helsinki blocks crossings

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Colombian President Gustavo Petro, visiting Venezuela on Saturday, said he had proposed to the United States that it pay an "economic stabilization" bonus to Venezuelan migrants who stop in Colombia en route to the U.S.
articles.title: Colombia's Petro says he proposed U.S. pay bonuses to Venezuelan migrants

articles.author: Timour Azhari
articles.description: Iraq's Kataeb Hezbollah (KH) militia, a powerful armed faction with close ties to Iran, brushed off U.S. sanctions on the group over attacks against U.S. forces in Iraq and Syria and said on Saturday such strikes aimed to "drain the enemy".
articles.title: Iraq's Kataeb Hezbollah says attacks aim to 'drain' US, sanctions 'ridiculous'

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi, James Mackenzie
articles.description: Israel prepared on Sunday to expand its offensive against Hamas militants to southern Gaza after air strikes killed dozens of Palestinians, including civilians reported to be sheltering at two schools.
articles.title: Israeli air strikes kill 47 in southern Gaza ahead of offensive against Hamas

articles.author: Maria Starkova, Elaine Monaghan
articles.description: President Volodymyr Zelenskiy has sanctioned 37 Russian groups and 108 people including a former prime minister and a former education minister and said he aimed to fight wartime abductions of children from Ukraine and other "Russian terror".
articles.title: Zelenskiy slaps sanctions on 108 people, 37 Russian groups

articles.author: Maximilian Heath
articles.description: Argentina will vote in a run-off presidential election on Sunday, with Peronist Economy Minister Sergio Massa taking on libertarian outsider Javier Milei to determine the future of the region's second largest economy.
articles.title: Explainer: What you need to know about Argentina's presidential election run-off
